# 7. 後悔のないように

Airi: Way to go, Haruka...! It took her barely a second to climb that wall...
Minori: She really is the best. I wouldn't even know where to start climbing!
Shizuku: Me neither. Her ability to make split-second decisions really is remarkable.
Airi: Not quite the commentary I was expecting, but this is where the real test begins!
Comments: <Can she do it...?> <You can do it, Haruka!> <We're all watching you!>
Airi: Everyone's cheering for you, Haruka! You've gotta clinch victory here!
Commentator: <Alright, this is the final obstacle our competitor is going to face. The hanging poles!>
Commentator: <She will need to jump from pole to pole by swinging her body like a pendulum! Having to hang above a pool will also add an extra layer of fear!>
Commentator: <There are three poles in total. This is by far the most difficult obstacle! Will she be able to conquer it?!>
Haruka: (There's about a one-and-a-half meter gap between the poles. I have to get my jumps just right. If I go too far or come up short, I'll fall in.)
Haruka: (Use your back and core muscles to swing your body and jump. Here comes... The first one!)
Audience: Oh, that was a pretty clean jump!
Audience: I didn't know Haruka could do stuff like this!
Haruka: (Yes...!)
Haruka: (I have a good idea of how to jump now... And I'm moving at a good place.)
Haruka: (If I can keep this up, then we might finish with the best time...! I need to maintain this momentum and...!)
Akito: ...! The wind...!
Haruka: N-No...!
Haruka: (That gust was so strong. I missed my chance to jump...)
Commentator: <That gust came out of nowhere!>
Commentator: <She didn't fall, but she finds herself stuck at the second section!>
Haruka: (I thought I could use the momentum I had to keep going, but that's all gone out the window...)
Haruka: (No, it's okay!)
Haruka: (Just swing your body, build up momentum and jump...)
Haruka: (Now...!)
Commentator: <She's made the second jump!>
Tsukasa: You're doing great, Kiritani!
An: Th-Thank goodness...! Just one to go! You can do it!
Haruka: (Okay, use this momentum to...!)
Haruka: Huh?! Again...?!
Haruka: (If I jump now, the wind will send me off course...! I need this gust to calm a little before...)
Commentator: <No, she's stopped again! This gust really is paralyzing! Is this it for her...?!>
Haruka: ...
An: Haruka...
Haruka: (I might be able to go now, but...)
Haruka: (What do I do...?)
Haruka: (The final part is just a jump from the pole to the landing area, but I'll have to fly at least two meters.)
Haruka: (I'll have to swing myself even harder than before in order to make it to the end.)
Audience: Is Haruka okay...? Can she make that jump?
Haruka: (My arms are starting to get really sore...)
Haruka: (Creating enough momentum to make that two-meter jump seems next to impossible at this point.)
Haruka: (But...)
An: Go, Haruka! Swing and fly!
Haruka: An...?
An: If you give up now, then you'll regret it for the rest of your life! So, swing and jump!
An: Help me out, Akito, Tenma! She'll succeed if we give her enough support!
Tsukasa: You can do it, Kiritani!
Akito: Just swing! You can make that jump easy!
Haruka: Everyone...
Haruka: (Right. The three of us did all that training just for this day.)
Haruka: (Also...)
Audience: Go! Fly! Just fly!
Audience: You can do it, Haruka! We're all rooting for you!
Haruka: (They all believe that I can do this.)
Haruka: (I have to fly and spread hope to them!)
Haruka: (First, I need to build back up some momentum...!)
Haruka: (Use your back and core muscles to swing your body and jump...)
Haruka: (Now!)
Audience: Oh, she jumped...!
Audience: You can do it!
Haruka: (Please, give me wings!)
An: Haruka...!
Akito: Sh-She made it...!
Tsukasa: Whoaaaa! Kiritaniiiii!
An: Way to go, Haruka! That was awesome!
Audience: She did it...! That was so cool!!
Haruka: Huff...! Huff...! I made it...!
Haruka: (Now I just need to press the button and...!)
Commentator: <What a miraculous jump! She's now using every last ounce of energy she has left to reach the finish line!>
Akito: Run, Kiritani!
Tsukasa & An: Go!
Commentator: <She's about to press the button...>
Haruka: Huff... Huff... There!
Commentator: <She finished!>
Commentator: <Despite everything they had to overcome, our ninth group still managed to finish. With a time of...!>
